  "text": "[25] The height of the boundary layer is parameterized to give a diurnal profile as described in [CITATION_1] . The value for the eddy diffusion coefficient K z is dependent on time, t, and on height, z. The nocturnal inversion is set to 100 metres altitude with K z fixed at 3.0 Â 10 3 cm 2 s À1 within that layer. Above 100 metres K z is set to 1.0 Â 10 2 cm 2 s À1 . The behavior of the boundary layer during daytime is parameterized using the time-dependent function for K z given by [CITATION_2] . An exponential height dependence is included. The well mixed boundary layer starts forming at 08:30, which compares well with the measurements (Figure 3) , and reaches its maximum of 1650 metres at 13:00, with K z reaching 1.0H10 6 cm 2 s À1 above 1000 metres. This produces good agreement with the observed diurnal pattern of measured species, including SO 2 . The top of the model is in the free troposphere at 1850 meters. There are 22 vertical layers, with increasing resolution at lower altitudes.",
